HEADWORD: Highflying
<hw>High"fly`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Extravagant in opinions or ambition.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Highflying</xex>, arbitrary kings.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Flying at a high altitude; -- of
airplanes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having an excessively high cost or perceived value;
temporarily very successful; -- of objects with respect to a market and
people in their occupations; <as>as, <ex>highflying</ex> internet
stocks; <ex>highflying</ex> executives moving between
companies</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>High-go</ent>⟦br⟧
